  "body": "Sometimes, `buildler compile` doesn't compile, and thinks everything is OK.\r\nHere's a repro (though there are cases where it doesn't compile even without removing the artifacts)\r\n```\r\ngit clone https://github.com/opengsn/gsn-with-ethers.git && cd gsn-with-ethers\r\n$ yarn install --ignore-optional\r\n...\r\nâœ¨  Done in 26.52s.\r\n$ bdl compile\r\nCompiling...\r\nDownloading compiler version 0.5.16\r\nCompiled 6 contracts successfully\r\n```\r\n^^^ (first compilation went OK)\r\n```\r\n$ bdl compile\r\nAll contracts have already been compiled, skipping compilation.\r\n```\r\n^^^ (cache up to date. OK)\r\n```\r\n$ rm -rf artifacts/\r\n$ bdl compile\r\nAll contracts have already been compiled, skipping compilation.\r\n```\r\n## ^^^ ERROR: should compile if no artifacts.\r\n```\r\n $ touch contracts/*\r\n$ bdl compile\r\nCompiling...\r\nCompiled 6 contracts successfully\r\n```\r\n^^^ after touch - OK",
